Bluprints for OpenESP
=====================

A blueprint is a complete example configuration for OpenESP, to demonstrate a particular usecase.

A blueprint is simply a complete set of configs, data and examples to illustrate an example usecase.
The blueprint typically includes:
* $OPENESP_HOME/conf/solr/<bpname> : Solr core config
* $OPENESP_HOME/conf/solr/solr.xml : The new core is added to solr.xml
* $OPENESP_HOME/blueprints/